caption: Someone correct me if I’m wrong, but I don’t think a pepper steak stir fry should look like beef soup...Steak is also overcooked like crazy. Definitely don’t order this dish, but I do recommend their noodle dishes instead.

Ordered through grubhub. Food is great! I finally found my favorite Thai restaurant in the area after I moved. Massamun curry was the best Thai curry I've had. My husband had orange chicken and he said it's his favorite OC!

What awesome service. I called to ask a question about Gluten Free, then placed my order online. After I submitted my order, the restaurant immediately called to confirm my order because I ordered items that were not gluten free. One item, I assumed was GF, and it wasn’t but they were able to make it GF for me. The other item was for someone else that isn’t GF. The point is that they realized it was me, and called to check and offer the modification. That’s service that I appreciate. Thank you!

This place charged me, without my permission, $3 to substitute American broccoli for Chinese broccoli. Done this substitution a ton. Never had an up charge. Also, just looked it up and American broccoli is LESS expensive than Chinese broccoli. Hope they enjoyed their 3 extra dollars (that I got back from Door Dash anyway) because I will NEVER be back

I kid you not they delivered hot delicious food in a mere 14 minutes from the time I ordered. I live only a mile away, but still, I wouldn't expect this short of a turn around from a restaurant just across the street. Highly recommend ordering directly from their website (10% off first order) and ordering their Paht Siew. Between time delivered and the fact that their Paht Siew was one of the best I've had in Chicago, I will definitely be ordering from here again.

Sad that I can’t find a good Thai place in bucktown. I thought this might be the one as it had the best reviews but I got a panang curry that was completely flavorless. I get panang almost every time I get Thai and I don’t think I’ve ever had one this bad. Eating it with rice I couldn’t even tell it had panang curry on it, it was just very bland and tasted watered down to oblivion. The papaya salad wasn’t fresh; all the cherry tomatoes were mushy and wrinkly. For a Thai restaurant on the pricier end I was totally disappointed
Pad thai is always solid.

Wow! Shockingly horrible. They threw uncooked slabs of tofu in the curry- which has a horrendous texture. Who doesn’t cook the tofu first?? The paht thai had zero flavor and looked like it had been sitting around for a few hours, wasn’t even remotely warm, really didn’t even resemble paht thai. The drunken noodles looked like regurgitated stew and also had little flavor. This was so unbelievably bad. I’ve gotten better Thai in Kansas for crying out loud. So disappointed. Never again.

Ordered from here for the first time today and loved it!!! Delicious food. Ordered through Google and they even called when the order was ready. I just wish they had descriptions of the vegetarian items on their menu!

I don't normally or ever leave reviews. In fact, this is my second . I have tried dozens of Thai places and I Usally order same thing. Beef Salad, Thai ice tea and some sort of appetizer. This place has set a bar and standard for me. The Beef Salad was THEE freshest beef salad I ever had. The meat was cooks excellent nice char the greens were so fresh. I felt like I picked them from a garden.  The tea was great and the appetizer baby egg rolls were on point. To the owners and Head Chef. Great work! I did order via Uber Eats and my order came in tact and on time and the beef was still warm! I may be switching to this place. While it is pricy...to me it's worth it.
We had pad thai and drunken noodles. Not bad, but lacked much in the way of flavor, the pad thai was very bland.
Some of the most consistent and delicious Thai food I've had in the city. Love their COVID setup for takeout orders too.
Wow, definitely my favorite Thai food in the city. We had massaman curry and paht thai and everything was so delicious. Look forward to trying more on their menu.
Wow! Best Massaman curry I've ever had. Excellent spring rolls (summer wraps). Yum yum!!!!
This place is great. Amazing food, reasonably priced, updated interior, fast service. Somehow, there never seems to be a wait.

Best orange chicken in the city, if not the best thai in the city.  Everything else I've tried has been great too.  High quality food, not the typical thai/chinese at a lot of other places.  Quick delivery (through their own website, not through GrubHub, etc.)  Every meal I've had from here has been great, but hooh boy, their orange chicken takes the cake.
Reliable for takeout! Flavorful and as expected.
Great food and ambience. Really nice staff.
Live close by and frequently eat here. Always kind people and great food and service.
Best Tom Yum Soup ever!
Love and unique place
Service was horrible.  We waited about an hour just to receive our drinks and it was nowhere near packed.
Very kind staff. The dessert was the most flavor of the meal. Corking fee  per person is kinda lame.
Took too long to prepare our food. Food was tasteless and expensive.
New Favorite spot, Great for take out! The Massumun Curry is Ridiculous...Ridicuoulsy good. Such a nice touch with the coconut milk added. Love it and will be back!
Excellent food, very good service, very nice atmosphere
Delicious food and great staff!

We were entertaining guest from UK and so it was a chance we were taking, as it was our first time there. Good was good, service was cold, charge $2.50 for a small bowl of rice which was not even filled. Great Ambience..no reason to go agian.sorry
Great food with excellent service
Super fresh food, really well priced and service was great. Will be returning.
Good vegitarian menu
Ordered a pad Thai to go and was unsatisfied, no sauce and thin clumps of noodles :(
Good curry. Cocktails were surprisingly great.
Very very good Thai food, in a beautifully designed environment, with very nice and respectful service. You won't regret this place

Delicious ....I’ve gone back several times now to try their curry dishes. So, good. Rich, creamy sauce with some added heat..., oh man,I’m hooked! Will be back to try more. Prompt service and friendly folks. Thanks guys !

I've been a customer of Silom 12 for a while - both in restaurant and delivery - and the last time I ordered delivery I was sent spring rolls with improperly cooked shrimp.  This gave me food poisoning, and the next day the manager of the restaurant came to pick up the unfinished dish because he didn't believe when I called that I was telling the truth.  Seeing the uncooked shrimp for himself, he apologized, told me that their chef refused to accept that he hadn't cooked the food properly and left.  I hadn't ordered from them for a long time because of this disagreeable experience, but today I decided to order.  I figured I'd be safe if I didn't order seafood.  About half an hour after placing my order, I received an email saying that it had been cancelled.  When I called the restaurant to ask why, I was told that the chef would no longer serve me because of what happened the last time I ordered.  I think this tells you everything you need to know about the service here.  They won't take responsibility when they make a mistake, and when you give them a second chance they offend you for a second time.  This restaurant doesn't deserve to be in business.

Just ordered from GrubHub here, first time visiting Chicago & they seemed like they had pretty decent reviews. I ordered Pad Thai and Drunken Noodles. As soon as I opened my Pad Thai I got a weird smell. I tried it and immediately got the taste of soapy mildew. After a 8 hour plane ride and craving good Thai, I’m extremely disappointed. I would not recommend.
The red curry and chicken pad Thai is the best thing to ever grace my mouth and taste buds. I’m not kidding, it’s like cr*ck. I’ve had this every night for 3 nights still want more
BYOB, the ambience it’s nice and relaxing and the food is good. Specially the appetizer/starters.
Awesome food and drinks

Great place for Thai dining. The portions are more than ample and the flavors are excellent. The decor is appropriate for casual dining or a formal evening. Service was attentive. We went during the early evening so there was another street parking. We'll go again.
Always fresh and nice dining room.not too pricey but good quality!
It was like being in Thailand. Great Tum Yum soup.  The best Pad Thai out side of the bus stop out side Bancock.

There is a lot of variety here and everything I have tried has been made well and with quality ingredients. Their takeout/delivery is as good as their dine-in and it doesn't suffer in transit. This place has been around for years but I have only tried it twice and recently but I'll definitely go back. It's always nice to have a solid option when you don't know what to eat but want it to be good.

I loved this place! The food is AWESOME and well worth the money. The ambience is very calming, making it a great place to have dinner with a group of friends or a romantic dinner with that special someone in your life.

Ordered here as it's our go to place for Thai food,  delicious fresh Obrien and good portions. Super fast delivery. Like Jimmy John's fast .  I was really disappointed though when my panang noodle arrived as it was so watered down and tasteless. I called to ask for a redo. They complied with this request but almost grudgingly.  Told me it was because I had asked for mild they pour coconut water in it.  It was awful this way so don't request mild! It took an hour for the redo to arrive and it was still quite watered down just not as bland.  I'm going to look elsewhere for Thai food.  The meat was also boiled and tough it used to be better.
Fantastic food, service, and ambiance

They play stupid cover songs. I've given this place three times to get a better review from me. It's essentially watered down Thai food. No flavor, no spice. I can see that most of the reviews on here are from people who can't handle spice or flavor. The good rating misled me into trying this place. It's relatively close to me. About a thirteen minute walk, but I won't be coming here again.  I ordered all specials. The tiger cry steak, the pork shank, and the soft shell crab entree. The pork was dry. The steak sat on a bed of green beans and they were bland as hell. The soft shell crab was the best. And it had spice, but it's crazy I have to go to a place three times to be satisfied. However, if you can't handle spice, this place is perfect for you.
Definitely one of the best restaurants in the area.
Food very good. Different I had the softshell crab. A little too much veggies but it was delicious.
Good scene for tasty Thai food. Cool place to meet and catch up with coworkers. Service is typically great. The bill was decent.
Great Thai ! Awesome Pad Thai
Great Thai in Chicago!
Went for daughters 15th birthday with some school friends.  Great food and the orange chicken is just lovely. I alsi alao have to have the patang curry. Cheap also.
The fried chicken thai dish is absolutely amazing! Definitely will go again just to order that.

I stopped in here for dinner after a hankering for thai food and was not disappointed. The kao soi dish caught my eye after the menu called it a north Thailand favorite, so I decided to try something new. I am very glad I did. This thing rivaled the best thai dishes I have had. It was kind of like a mixture of ramen and panang curry and delicious to the last drop. I will be returning to get this again.
Great food and smoothies.

Good food. Good prices. Good staff. Good service. Great place for thai food in the area. Must: coconut sticky rice and mango for dessert. The decor is modern and the vibe is intimate though they do have quite the space, not huge, but you don't feel cramped at all. Definitely worth checking out.

Great date spot. Lots to look at and the aesthetic is really fun. - If you’ve never been here before, get the Paht Thai. Their stir-fry choices aren’t as delicious. - Between delivery and just going to the restaurant, you should go to the restaurant. The food tastes better and you’re in a great atmosphere. Would highly recommend! - Pro tip: get the sticky rice. It’s really good!
Friendly staff.
My favorite take out. Very fast delivery. The best crab Rangoon and orange chicken
I was in town for a few days. Had dinner at Silom two of the nights. My colleague and I were a happy customer both times.

Would definitely recommend! The restaurant has a nice aesthetic! Service is great and the food is also great! The owner let us use the space for our small wedding gathering and the service was outstanding couldn’t have asked for a better place to celebrate! The food is delicious like mentioned previously, all of our guests enjoyed and were very satisfied! A must place to visit!!!
Been going here forever, absolutely love it! Clean space, polite people, delish food.
Great curries and noodles. One of our regular go-to consisted take out joints!
Plenty of vegetarian options.
Dependable, tasty Thai food, friendly, fast service. Dine in or carry out. Delicious dishes.

Although the staff is perfectly nice and there’s nothing wrong with the food, the atmosphere is very unwelcoming. Everything is clean, but the decor is all hard surfaces, straight lines. It feels totally sterile and charmless. I felt cold and uncomfortable with an odd playlist and some over the top holiday decorations. Ultimately there didn’t seem to be any strong pull to come back, no special dish or exciting menu and nothing enjoyable about the atmosphere.

The food in this place is delicious! Silom has a unique, quiet, romantic atmosphere. I always look forward to ending my work week at that place because it’s cozy and the service is great. The vegetable tofu soup is a must, but you have to like spicy. Cashew chicken, pad thai, all delicious!
Excellent food and service. We went on a Sunday night. Everything was reasonably priced and the menu selections were fantastic. I highly recommend Silom 12.
Good byob date spot
Delicious! I really like this place. I've been here 3 times in the past 2 months. Quiet, relaxed ambiance. Family friendly, group friendly. BYOB also.
A lot of solid offerings here. Chicken and sweet potato buns were pretty good, as were the spring rolls and fried chicken balls (forgot the name).
Very impressed by their service and exquisite food. Chris was very pleasant and made sure we had an awesome experience. Thanks Chris!
Really nice date night spot. Good food, mellow environment and BYOB. The staff was super pleasant too.
The bartender was cute, I think his name was thor. best Midori sour I’ve ever had.
Good date spot with byob

The pad thia is my go to when I have a craving, it's wonderful. If you order through their website you get some bonuses after enough orders. Also, I've ordered pick up from here probably 25 times throughout the last couple years and they have always gotten my order right.

We were trying to go to irazu but the wait was too long and we were hungry. Stumbled over here and what a delightful surprise. The food was delicious,  service was friendly and attentive, it was reasonably priced amd it had a chill atmosphere. I'll definitely go back.
Great Thai dining!
Good Thai food and nice ambiance. Service was good too. Wasn't too happy with my Pad Thai as it had way too much sauce on it, but overall a good experiencr.
Great food and service + BYOB.
Panang curry is delicious!
We literally had the place to ourselves and it was incredibly lovely. This place is underrated
The food, atmosphere, and staff was excellent. I highly recommend it.
This place is alway my to-go spot when im craving some good pad-thai and their orange chicken is amazing to say the least! They are open till Midnight which helps alot for those late night cravings!
Good food and good ambiance
Great little spot for awesome Thai
Great neighborhood Thai restaurant -- good food, pricing and service
Good Thai food overall.  Crab Rangoon was excellent.  Mee krob and green curry rice was gloppy.
Good service, good food. The basil duck was fairly dry and tough

I dont get all these rave reviews. We did delivery and It was some of the worst thai food i've ever had. The  Penang curry was watery and bland. I basically ate the meat which wasnt very good either and threw out the rest it was pretty bad. The pot stickers were ok.  The G.F. didnt care for her dish either she ordered some sort of soup. This was our second time ordering and the first wasnt much better.  They should be embarrassed I could have done better and im an awful cook. needless to say never again.

Easily a 5 star review here after consistent quality across the menu. Finally giving my two cents on execution on this Americanized Thai restaurant after getting the Silom Wings which were I think the best non-spicy wings I've had yet.
Great food
Decent food. Not that spicy though
this place is okay, good service but not the best thai
Great food. BYOB.
I ordered green curry chicken and it was very good. Environment is pleasant and clean.

Recently discovered this place, and loved it. It's right off the 606. I had the lime chicken noodles and it was one of the best Thai dishes I've ever had. I will definitely be ordering from here again.
interesting seating and good food
Consistently good good, often with unique twists. I had been blindly ordering delivery from here for years only to realize to my surprise that it's a nice looking space too!

The current 4+ star rating does NOT reflect the quality of the food served. I ordered Paht Siew. The noodles were tremendously over cooked, Chinese broccoli was 2 little old slivers with a few morsels of green beans substituted, and the sweet soy sauce was seemingly a thickened fish sauce. My guest ordered some curry. While the flavor was ok, the texture was grainy, indicating it was from curry powder, not a paste. The only thing that I can agree with from other ratings is that the service was fast. It should have been--there were only two other diners.
Food was really good. Service was fast. The location is a bit out of the way.

Favorite Thai food in Chicago. Great for dine in or takeout and it's byob too! Our go-to dishes are the pad thai, masamam curry and drunken noodles, and we normally get some of the crab Rangoon too (which they make with filo pastry)

I. Love. This. Place. It is amazing! I have ordered from here multiple times and they have yet to let me down. Panang Curry is awesome. Crab Rangoons are so good that it converted my crab rangoon-hating roommate into a crab rangoon-lover. Drunk noodles are ridiculously good.  Delivery is always quicker than the grubhub estimate by like 20 or 30 minutes. Plus their delivery guy is always smiling and friendly.
One of the best in Logan

This place is one of the best Thai restaurants in the city. A lot of great food for a decent price. Red and Panang curry are great, but I haven't tried the others yet. Love the tuna appetizer and the sticky rice
Food was not great and definitely not worth 4.5 stars
They were very speedy with there sevice and were very friendly people too! Loved it and would definitely make the trip for it again.
One of the best casual thai places in the city. Can do anything from big group reservations to quick takeout byob too! Loved the curries.

This is an Americanized Thai place.  Basil Chicken tasted like chicken and soy sauce.  Pad Thai mushy and too sweet, not enough fish sauce flavor.  If you never had authentic Thai food, this restaurant will serve you just fine.  It's a clean restaurant with good service.
Fantastic food
Wow, great food, great service, and..... The right price, which is hard to come by around here.  Definitely hit this place up!

the restaurant was modern, roomy, decorated tastefully, and spotlessly clean (including the bathroom) and my finger came out super quickly and was wonderful. the service was great, almost to the point of reverence. and the prices were good. also had no issues parking... although I wish the city had done a better job of de-iceing the sidewalk.

I know what your thinking -- most all Thai tastes pretty much the same.... well not if you're at Silom 12.  This is some of the best, freshest and most authentic Thai food in the city.  It is truly a cut above the rest.
Great peanut sauce and pad thia.  Their crab Rangoon are amazing as well.
Delicious, great service, nice atmosphere. Recommend

This is the best Thai place in the area! Reasonably priced and always excellent, large helpings that requires to usually take some home, and full of flavor. We've tried a variety of glass noodle dishes and curry and love them all! Also it's BYOB.

Look no further! This is a BYOB thai restaurant! For an additional $2/person, you can bring your own bottle of wine to enjoy with your meal. Make sure you grab a bottle of wine from across the street at Red and White Wines.  The Tom Yung Goong soup is delicious, but beware: there are slices of jalapeño peppers in there. We also loved the Duck Delight! The duck is cooked nicely and perfectly crispy. Also you can't ever go wrong with ordering Pad Thai.  TIP: If you pay in cash, you get 10% off your bill.
Best Thai food in the 'hood. Try the Crispy Tofu Salad! The staff is great! Very friendly, attentive without being intrusive.
Best Thai food in the area. Big portions, reasonable prices, and most importantly great flavor. We get this food at least once a month.

Clean and modern eating area. Every dish I've had here has been full of flavor and made with fresh ingredients. Recommend the spicy fried rice, drunken noodles and the Panang Cocunut Curry. The curry was a little sweet and a little spicy...delicious!
Delicious food and quick service! Drunken noodles, red curry and garlic chicken were all great.

I'd say the food was about average-good, but the service was very nice, and the restaurant is a comfortable place. It's bigger than it looks from the entrance, with two separate rooms. We tried a few basics, pad thai and drunken noodles, and a big chicken dish, and all were good. My drunken noodles were enough for a second meal. Food came quickly. Plenty of parking around.

Really nice, creative decor plus al fresco dining.  The menu is a nice twist from the usual Thai place, and prices are quite reasonable.  I had the orange chicken and it was one of the best I've had, plus beautiful presentation.

A little pricier than some of the other Thai restaurants in the area, but the food seems to have a slightly different take on the traditional dishes.  I got a spicy fried rice that was very good and distinctly different from other restaurants in the area.  Also, the only Thai restaurant I have been where they give you some free nosh for the table, and the interior is very upscale with a nice bar.

I stopped by with friends for dinner and ordered shrimp in a spicy clear curry that was good but not good enough that I'd eat the sauce alone; my date's red curry was more my style. Good service, if slightly awkward, and I'd give Silom 12 another try. Their menu went much deeper than most Thai places I've been, which makes me think they have more authentic and interesting options.

Delivery came when it was supposed to. I ordered some ramen and some sweet potato curry. The ramen outside of the noodles themselves was fantastic, best broth and vegetables I've had in a long time. The Massaman sweet potato curry on the other hand tasted like pure vomit. It was way too sweet and left a bad taste in your mouth which was too similar to puke (curry had puke texture as well). I didn't want to waste my money, but was forced to throw the entire curry in the garbage because I couldn't take it anymore.

The food and staff at Silom were excellent. Be careful when ordering though, becuase they give you huge portions. I had the Talapia and I swear they gave me the whold fish and whatever you do, try the Hot and Sour soup. Its taste great and could be a meal by itself its so hearty. When I visited I had been drinking all weekend and was craving a crispy smoothy something with cucumbers or apples. Turns out they had a smoothie menu! If you are in the Bucktown area you have to eat hear and take in a show at Gorilla Tango a block north.

I've never been into Silom 12, so I can't comment o the decor. Though I have recieved delivery many times. The food is phenomenal The pad thai is to die for. Here's what I recommend...  Starters: Larb tob gui chai and crab rangoon Soups: Tom kar gai Entrees: Panang coconut and shrimp pad thi

Unique twist to old school thai.  Food was tasty, service fast, good ambiance.  Now has bar, charged $2 a person for byob beer... Seemed reasonable.  Classy place where we would bring group of friends.  Will come back.

My girlfriend and I both greatly enjoyed the service. The two young men who served us seemed to want to make us happy as well as well fed. From here my girlfriend and I differ in our opinions. While we both thoroughly enjoyed the decor, she was not a big fan of the music when we first sat down, calling it elevator music. However, I loved it and practically danced through the meal. My plate, the Asparagus and Shrimp stir fry, was amazing. Vegetables were crisp and fresh, the shrimp had real flavor. They even suggested a beer which tasted very good with the food. However, my girlfriend had the Pad Thai. While it was very flavorful, it wasn't what she was expecting. The noodles seemed different, and the sauce wasn't plentiful enough. Despite that, we enjoyed an app, entrees, a couple drinks, and fried ice cream. I say two thumbs way, way up. She says one thumb up, but still quite good.
Delivery is prompt.  The food is really quite good.  Their drunken noodles with beef are just about perfect.

I only went once for take out. I ordered drunken noodles with chicken and basil beef, typical Thai, nothing fancy. The restaurant itself is quite comtemporary and feels like a good place for a small appetizer and some BYOB drinks. But the food is hardly as nice as the atmosphere. Average taste and small portion. My chicken is blank and doesn't have ANY taste at all.
